{"content":{"body":"A mictotask check point only takes effect when the js stack is empty. When you call dispatchEvent from within a script you are still inside a js stack ","m.relates_to":{"event_id":"$J5oBFMPGzUjAGpP1jhoTbulgJNktJ1RZKOpr_NMEi78","is_falling_back":true,"m.in_reply_to":{"event_id":"$J5oBFMPGzUjAGpP1jhoTbulgJNktJ1RZKOpr_NMEi78"},"rel_type":"m.thread"},"msgtype":"m.text"},"ts":1774854979353,"senderName":"Noam Rosenthal","senderId":"@noamr:matrix.org","id":"$W5l0KQ2xQAnQORVinMJElKWaLGI1I0HvrKkKopyhjuc"},
{"content":{"body":"Event dispatching itself is synchronous, however most/some events are fired within their own task and the spec would say something like \"queue a task to fire an event\". ","m.relates_to":{"event_id":"$J5oBFMPGzUjAGpP1jhoTbulgJNktJ1RZKOpr_NMEi78","is_falling_back":true,"m.in_reply_to":{"event_id":"$W5l0KQ2xQAnQORVinMJElKWaLGI1I0HvrKkKopyhjuc"},"rel_type":"m.thread"},"msgtype":"m.text"},"ts":1774855058808,"senderName":"Noam Rosenthal","senderId":"@noamr:matrix.org","id":"$JWskyUNeoQqlVfk-TsXlq6Fms6Mp-RmlMX1jlwZiGys"},
